interview_date: RedCap event registration date when copied to IntraDB (rounded down to nearest Quarter)
unrelated_subset: Is subject unrelated to others in HCA/HCD?
HiResHpT2_Count: # of High Resolution Hippocampal T2w scans
QC_Issue_Codes: Issues identified in imaging QC: A=anatomical anomaly, B1a=white surface too deep, B1b=white surface too superficial, B1c=other white surface imperfection, B2a=pial surface too deep, B2b=pial surface too superficial (blood vessel/sinus), B2c=pial surface too superficial (dural inclusion), B2d=other pial surface imperfection, B3=VR space white/pial surface errors, C1=myelin map non-uniformity, C2=low myelin map quality due to T1/T2 scan quality, C3=myelin map aging effects, C4=low myelin map quality due to motion/large B1+ effects, C5=myelin map MSMSulc misidentified central sulcus, D1=manually edited wm.mgz, D2=manually edited brainmask.mgz, D3=manually added control points
